summary: Who is the Justin Timberlake of the andi mack cast? Who do you think will be the biggest star from the show 10 years from now
question: Who is the Justin Timberlake of the andi mack cast? Who do you think will be the biggest star from the show 10 years from now
answer:
That’s a really weird comparison to make. Are you asking this in the context of Justin Timberlake being a former Mickey Mouse Club star? Because if so - I would argue that he is not the “biggest star from the show” given the fact that he was on it with Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, and Ryan Gosling - all of whom are highly successful. 

Anyways. I’ve said it before - I think all of the kids have the potential to succeed in whatever they want to do, but the image of success is different for everyone. Asher can be a successful pop star, while Josh can be a successful politician, while Sofia can be a successful dancer, while Peyton can be a successful actress, while Luke can be a successful environmentalist. Like. These people are all so young that it’s strange for me to even think about any of them being ~better~ than the others when we don’t even know what direction they’ll go ya know.

That being said, I think that Asher and Sofia are clearly putting the most work into branding themselves for success. Asher already making a name for himself in film and music, and being a conventionally attractive and charming white boy will definitely play in his career’s favor. Sofia is a power-house working in dance, television, music, animation, film, production, etc. and I have full faith that if she continues with the same drive she has right now - nothing will stop her. 

That’s not to say that the others won’t be successful in a decade, I’m sure they will, but Asher and Sofia both seem to be actively trying to extend their careers in the industry ig.

summary: I’ve always wondered: Does “single cam” literally mean one camera? If yes, how do they get all these different angles? By...
question: I’ve always wondered: Does “single cam” literally mean one camera? If yes, how do they get all these different angles? By shooting scenes multiple times?
answer:
A single-cam show does not necessarily mean that they only use one camera, sometimes there are multiple cameras. But they only shoot one angle at a time, and then shoot the same scene (or part of a scene) again from a different angle which allows more choices in editing room. 

A good example of a scene from Andi Mack to use would be Swing Set 2.0. They would have had to film the scene at least once with the camera pointed at Josh, then again with the camera pointed at Luke, and again for the wide shots. In most cases, they would film each scene and each angle multiple times anyway.

A multi-cam show means that they have multiple cameras filming the same scene simultaneously, each from different angles. When it comes to sit-coms, the main difference is really that multi-cam shows are usually filmed in front of a studio audience while single-cam shows are not. Single-cam is traditionally much more “movie” like, while multi-cam shows are more “TV”.

summary: Kugel and challah are not necessarily religious food. Yes they are related with jewish culture, but i'm polish, not jew and i...
question: Kugel and challah are not necessarily religious food. Yes they are related with jewish culture, but i'm polish, not jew and i can be those things in every grocery shop
answer:
Well, yeah, of course, you can buy these foods from any grocery store and get them if you’re not Jewish but they still have religious meaning. When I was researching, I discovered the Challah is brimming with religious symbolism. Firstly, it is eaten before Yom Kippur (a day of fasting and atonement) and the word comes from Hebrew and describes a divine biblical rule which states that a piece of the bread should be given to god as a gift and so many Jews still give a piece of their challah to their local kohanims (priests) during Sabbath (holy seventh day). Anyway, each shape of the Challah indicates something; the round loaf symbolizes continuity, three braids are for truth, peace and justice, there’s also bread that portrays the twelve tribes of Israel and so on and so forth.

As for the Kugel, it’s a Kugel and there’s a Yiddish proverb that states that the Shabbath without Kugel is like a bird without wings. Need I say more?

Anyone can get whatever food they want from a grocery store but certain food has religious meaning. It always has and always will.

For instance, Muslims eat dates to break their fast during Ramadan. You can get a date anywhere, in any grocery store, but a date has religious value to Muslims because Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) gave dates great importance and stated that opening your fast with a date was cleansing and a method of protection.

That’s my two cents. Sorry for the long response.

question: Wandi
answer:
Who clings to the other during scary movies? 

Andi ofc

Who asks weird questions in the middle of the night? 

Definitely Andi. And Walker makes a big effort to pretend that he’s not annoyed

Who falls asleep on the other? 

Walker falls asleep on Andi, she can’t sleep at regular hours and he tries to stay up with her but fails

Who eats the other’s uneaten pizza crusts?

Andi

Who talks smack(trash talks) while playing video games? 

I’ll go with both, they get very angry

Who would throw the other in the pool?

Andi would throw Walker first, but he would take revenge

Who is the better carer when the other is sick?

Andi

Who cooks normally? 

Walker (do you remember when Andi tried to make coffee and eggs for Bex?)

Who made the first move?

Walker, canonically

Who kissed who first? 

Walker kissed Andi first

How often do they fight and over what?

They get into silly arguments about unimportant stuff every day, but they rarely fight. When they do, it’s about each other’s attitudes (Andi thinks Walker should be more assertive, Walker thinks Andi overreacts and makes things about her)

Who’s the first one to fix things after a fight?

Walker, he can’t stand not being good with Andi

Who talks about the other more without noticing? 

Walker. A lot. (Andi does too but she notices it because Buffy points it out)

Who steals the other’s clothes?

Andi. She loves all of his art-themed shirts

Which of their friends is over-joyed shipper trash that they are together? 

Cyrus

summary: Do you think TJ line "i have layers" can he foreshadowing since Luke said we gonna learn a lot more about TJ?
question: Do you think TJ line "i have layers" can he foreshadowing since Luke said we gonna learn a lot more about TJ?
answer: I’m not sure if I would qualify it as “foreshadowing”, but I think that vague lines like that are definitely subtext. The same goes for “You don’t know me, I’ve got stuff” from the original swing scene. I think that “I have layers” was meant to be more light-hearted (because why else would they throw in an obvious Shrek reference). But I think that Luke’s comments about TJ and these subtextual references to the depth of his character in the show are both references to the rest of his storyline, which will focus on his sexuality and feelings for Cyrus.
